":"Toggle-Buttons","text":"Toggle Buttons","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The “toggle button” is a widely recognized user experience (UX) design concept. It is a button that exhibits two distinct states: a “normal” state and a “selected” state."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SnappTheming"},{"text":" supports toggle buttons out of the box with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiftUI"},{"text":", thanks to a helper library called ","type":"text"},{"code":"SnappThemingSwiftUIHelpers","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Let’s assume that we need to incorporate a toggle button within our application. The initial step involves defining distinct button styles for its normal and selected states. Let us denote the style for the normal state as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"toggleButton"},{"text":" and the style for the selected state as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"toggleButtonSelected"},{"type":"text","text":". Below is the code snippet that can be incorporated into our "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiftUI"},{"text":" view to support the toggling functionality:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["import SnappTheming","import SnappThemingSwiftUIHelpers","","struct ToggleButtonsView: View {","    @Environment(SnappThemingDeclaration.self) var declaration","    @State var isFirstSelected: Bool = false","    @State var isSecondSelected: Bool = false","","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            Button(\"Toggle 1\") {","                isFirstSelected.toggle()","            }","            .buttonStyle(declaration.buttonStyles.action, selected: declaration.buttonStyles.actionSelected)","            .selected(isFirstSelected)","","            Button(\"Toggle 2\") {","                isSecondSelected.toggle()","            }","            .buttonStyle(declaration.buttonStyles.action, selected: declaration.buttonStyles.actionSelected)","            .selected(isSecondSelected)","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":"(swift)"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/snapptheming.SnappTheming\/documentation\/SnappTheming"]]},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"title":"SnappThemingButtonStyleDeclarations","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Type Alias","fragments":[{"text":"typealias","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SnappThemingButtonStyleDeclarations"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SnappThemingButtonStyleDeclarations","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"typealias","modules":[{"name":"SnappTheming"}],"externalID":"s:12SnappTheming0aB23ButtonStyleDeclarationsa"},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/snapptheming\/snappthemingbuttonstyledeclarations"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manages button styles, including properties such as surface and text colors, border widths and colors, shapes, and typography for various button states."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/snapptheming.SnappTheming\/documentation\/SnappTheming\/SnappThemingButtonStyleDeclarations","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://snapptheming.SnappTheming/documentation/SnappTheming/SnappThemingButtonStyleRepresentation":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SnappThemingButtonStyleRepresentation","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"SnappThemingButtonStyleRepresentation","url":"\/documentation\/snapptheming\/snappthemingbuttonstylerepresentation","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SnappThemingButtonStyleRepresentation","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A representation of button style in the SnappTheming framework."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/snapptheming.SnappTheming\/documentation\/SnappTheming\/SnappThemingButtonStyleRepresentation"